														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2383725">
									

<p>No that's not correct. &quot;<em>Nexus</em>&quot; is fourth declension and the proper Latin plural would be &quot;<em>nexūs</em>&quot;. The &quot;i&quot; ending is for second declension nouns. We aren't writing in Latin though, but rather in English and therefore the regular plural is &quot;nexuses&quot; (although the dictionary also gives &quot;nexus&quot; as an irregular plural, presumably derived more directly from the Latin, if you prefer).</p>
<p>Like I said below: <strong>fake latinate plurals are almost never right.</strong></p>

