															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205783" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1443518995 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Sep 2015 09:29</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2383456">
									

<p>Pros:</p>
<ul>
<li>It is good to bring up Nexus and how they work out in the organisational structure of the Foundation.</li>
<li>I actually like the alternate Area Class system.</li>
</ul>
<p>Cons:</p>
<ul>
<li>I don't really see how Nexus are distinct from a localised SCP or an Anomalous Location.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-563438-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-563438-1')">1</a></sup> I believe the Nexus needs to be better (and explicitly in-story) defined for entries about it to flourish as a whole.</li>
</ul>
<p>Suggestion:</p>
<ul>
<li>An interesting aspect of Nexus is that it apparently requires a minimum of people and there appears to be an upper limit for it. Why is that so? If addressed, I believe it could make an impact that inspires others to consider this beyond Sloth's Pit.</li>
</ul>
